2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 237
BY REPRESENTATIVES OWEN, BRAUD, AND HORTON
CENSUS: Memorializes Congress to enact a provision in the National Defense
Authorization Act directing the Department of Defense to provide accurate on-base
population counts for the decennial census
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To memorialize the United States Congress to enact a provision in the National Defense
3 Authorization Act directing the Department of Defense to furnish official personnel
4 counts directly to the United States Census Bureau for military installations located
5 in the contiguous United States.
6 WHEREAS, Article I, Section 2 of the Constitution of the United States requires an
7 enumeration of the population of the United States every ten years; and
8 WHEREAS, accurate census counts are essential for fair apportionment of
9 congressional seats, proper allocation of federal funding, and accurate representation of
10 communities across the state; and
11 WHEREAS, Louisiana is home to three major military installations: Fort Polk,
12 Barksdale Air Force Base, and Naval Air Station Joint Reserve Base New Orleans, that
13 together house tens of thousands of active-duty military personnel, civilian employees, and
14 dependent family members; and
15 WHEREAS, historical census counts conducted by door-to-door enumeration on
16 these secure military installations have resulted in significant undercounts; and
17 WHEREAS, the 2020 Census reported seven thousand nine hundred fifty personnel,
18 spouses, dependents, and contractors residing on Fort Polk when the actual population
19 exceeded thirty-eight thousand; and
