1 WHEREAS, the Department of Defense and each installation's garrison personnel
2 offices maintain precise, daily counts of all soldiers, airmen, sailors, marines, civilian
3 employees, and dependent family members physically residing on base; and
4 WHEREAS, requiring the Department of Defense to provide these verified numbers
5 directly to the United States Census Bureau would eliminate the need for door-to-door
6 census workers on military installations, improve accuracy, create administrative
7 efficiencies, reduce costs, and allow census resources to be redirected to more complex
8 enumeration challenges elsewhere.
9 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
10 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby memorialize the United States Congress to include in
11 the National Defense Authorization Act a provision directing the Department of Defense to
12 furnish to the United States Census Bureau the exact number of military personnel, civilian
13 employees, and dependent family members residing on each military installation in the
14 contiguous United States during each decennial census.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
16 Speaker of the United States House of Representatives, the President of the United States
17 Senate, each member of the Louisiana congressional delegation, and the Secretary of
18 Defense.
